            <h2><strong style="color: black;">How to edit a Project</strong></h2>

            <hr></hr>

            <!--Step 1-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 1</h4>
                <img src="../images/step1ep.png" style="height: 70px; width: 150px;" alt="Step one image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-First, click on the "My Projects" icon located on the sidebar.</p>
                <p>-You will only be able to edit the projects that you are running.</p>  
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 2-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 2</h4>
                <img src="../images/step2ep.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-From the My Projects page, click the project name that you want to edit.</p> 
            </div>

            <br></br>

            <!--Step 3-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 3</h4>
                <img src="../images/step3ep.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-This is the page you will be able to edit many aspects of the project that was selected.</p>
                <p>-On this page, you will be able to see all items that are completed and need to be completed for this project.</p>
                <p>-You can click any of the check boxes if that task has been completed and the percentage complete will automatically adjust.</p>
                <p>The changes you make to the task will be automatically be saved.</p> 
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 4-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Transfer Project</h4>
                <img src="../images/step4ep.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-If you click the "Edit Run By" button as seen in the last step, you will be asked if you would like to transfer the project.</p>
                <p>Here, you can type your colleagues email or select them from the "select colleagues" button.</p>
                <p>-Once you select a colleague and click "Save Changes", the project will now no longer be ran by yourself and will be removed from your "My Projects" list.</p> 
                <p>A comment will be attached to the project showing who the project was transfered to and from.</p>  
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 5-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Edit Project Info</h4>
                <img src="../images/step5ep.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-If you select the "Edit Info" button as seen in step 3, you will be shown the project's name and the main contact's email</p>
                <p>-Here, you can edit the information assotiated with this project.</p>
                <p>-Once you have completed your changes, click the "Save Changes" button and the new information will be saved for this project.</p>     
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 6-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Delete Project</h4>
                <img src="../images/step6ep.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-If you wish to delete a project, click the "Delete" button located on the bottom right of the tasks table.</p>
                <p>-Once clicked, you will be asked if you are sure you want to delete the project.</p>
                <p>-If you click yes, you will be asked to input your password.</p>    
                <p>-If your password is correct, the project will be deleted and you will be redirected to your "My Projects" page.</p>
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 7-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Comments</h4>
                <img src="../images/step7ep.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-At the bottom of each project, you will be able to add a comment to your project.</p>
                <p>-In the comment bar, type your comment and click the "Comment" button to upload your comment which will be saved to this project.</p>
                <p>-If you wish to delete your comment, you can click the "x" located on the right side of your comment.</p>    
                <p>-Other users can comment on your project if they select your project in the "Active Projects" tab located on the sidebar.</p>
            </div>
         

